## Working in this folder

Agents, slash commands (`/recall`), and lifecycle hooks (SessionStart, PreToolUse, Stop) **only work when Claude Code is opened directly inside a project subfolder**. They are coupled to the git repo root and will not fire correctly from this wrapper folder.

To get full clagentic integration: open a project subfolder in Claude Code, or `cd` into it and start a new session.

## Builder rules (apply in all enrolled projects)

1. **Delegate code work to the Builder.** When the user asks you to write, edit, or refactor code, use the `clagentic-lite:builder` subagent — do not author code directly in the main session.

2. **Review with the Reviewer agent after staging, before opening a PR.** Use `clagentic-lite:reviewer` directly. Cross-vendor review is the load-bearing pattern; skipping it defeats the purpose of the harness.

3. **Never write to the default branch.** The pre-write-guard blocks it, but do not attempt it. Create a feature branch first.

4. **Gate before opening a PR.** Run `clagentic-lite gates ship` — it runs all blocking gates (secrets, deps, sast, review, adversarial, merge-gate) and opens the PR only if all pass.

5. **Never bypass security gates.** If `gitleaks`, `semgrep`, or `osv-scanner` block, fix the underlying issue. Do not add suppressions without a written justification in the commit message.

## Agents

| Agent | When to use |
|---|---|
| `clagentic-lite:builder` | Write, edit, or refactor code — the primary code author |
| `clagentic-lite:reviewer` | Review staged changes; cross-vendor second opinion after Builder completes work |
| `clagentic-lite:auditor` | Security narration on top of gitleaks/semgrep/osv findings |
| `clagentic-lite:merge-gate` | Final approve/refuse decision before opening a PR |
| `clagentic-lite:troubleshooter` | Diagnose a gate failure, hook error, or unexpected output — read-only |

## Slash commands

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `/recall` | Search session memory for prior decisions |
| `/eng-consult` | Multi-voice engineering panel — quality, security, SRE, UX review of a file or codebase |
| `/infosec-rt` | Security red team — attacker personas model exploit chains; returns a ranked hardening plan |

## Commands (from this wrapper level)

```sh
# Enrollment
clagentic-lite enroll <project-subfolder>     # enroll a project under this wrapper
clagentic-lite unenroll <project-subfolder>   # remove clagentic wiring from a project
clagentic-lite list                           # show all enrolled repos with status

# Diagnostics
clagentic-lite doctor                         # verify prereqs and enrolled-repo health

# Updates
clagentic-lite update                         # pull latest, re-stamp all enrolled repos
clagentic-lite update --restamp               # force re-stamp all managed artifacts
```

## Audit trail (per project)

```sh
# Query gate runs for a specific project
sqlite3 <project>/.clagentic/audit.db "SELECT ts, gate, outcome FROM gate_runs ORDER BY ts DESC LIMIT 20;"

# From inside the project folder:
clagentic-lite gates digest
clagentic-lite show gates [N]
clagentic-lite show memory [N]
```
